## Codebase Brain

This repo carries a committed agent brain in `.agents/`. Any coding agent (Claude Code,
Codex, Copilot) should consult it before changing code, and append to it when it learns
something durable.

- **Knowledge** — how this codebase works: `.agents/knowledge/`
  - `invariants.md` — **DO NOT break these.** Read first.
  - `architecture.md`, `structure.md`, `conventions.md`, `stack.md`,
    `integrations.md`, `testing.md`, `concerns.md`
- **Memory** — durable decisions & gotchas, one fact per file: `.agents/memory/`
  (index: `.agents/memory/MEMORY.md`)

## Working agreement

- Read `invariants.md` before editing; if a request would violate one, say so before doing it.
- Run it before claiming it works — evidence before assertions.
- When you learn something the next person would otherwise rediscover, record it in memory.

